FBIS4-770 "drafr073_c_94013" FBIS-AFR-94-073 Daily Report 14 Apr 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Further on Security Measures Further on Security Measures MB1404161294 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 1400 GMT 14 Apr 94 MB1404161294 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network English BFN [Text] The police have released a detailed report on security measures for the coming election. A police spokesman said in releasing the report in Pretoria that measures would be implemented nationally to prevent disturbances at polling stations. No weapons or firearms will be allowed within a 1,100-meter radius of voting stations, and people will be searched before being allowed in to vote. No party tents, political activity, flags, or banners will be allowed within the same radius. The polling stations will be searched for explosives or other undesirable objects before people will be allowed to go in, and only voters will be allowed within a 600-meter radius of polling centers.
